                                                                    <div class="moto-widget-text-content moto-widget-text-editable">
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Ah, Lord GOD! Behold, You have made the heavens and the earth by Your great power and outstretched arm. There is nothing too hard for You.”
                                                                           <b> Jeremiah 32:17 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Declaring the end from the beginning, And from ancient times things that are not yet done, Saying, “My counsel shall stand, And I will do all My pleasure,’”
                                                                            <b>Isaiah 46:10 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“I am the Alpha and the Omega, the Beginning and the End,” says the Lord, “who is and who was and who is to come, the Almighty.”
                                                                            <b>Revelation 1:8 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Omnipotence’s meaning derived from Latin is the ability to do all and have all power, having all the potency there is.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Omnipotence’s meaning derived from Anglo-Saxon is Almighty, meaning having an infinite and absolute plenitude of power.  Infinite and absolute can only refer to God.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">I was walking one day with a friend as we looked up in the sky and saw the moon was still visible.  My friend said, “oh look, the moon is late setting.”  I guess by the expression on my face my friend knew that was a nonsensical thought.  We laughed.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">In the beginning the omnipotent God Almighty, created the heavens and the earth and placed the sun, stars and moon in the heavens.  Each day they are precisely where they need to be without fail.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">He is not only the source of all power, He is power.  Without God there would be no power.
                                                                            Everything is held in place as He put it.  It is by His infinite and plenitude power that all exist as it is.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Have you ever said, “I can’t do this, I have no strength left.”  I thought so...because I have.  Our perspective of who we belong to, and who it is that loves us with an everlasting love is flawed.  In these times we must go back to His Omnipresence and surrender ourselves to our Omnipotent God allowing His power to flow through His presence to strengthen us to grasp the victory He desires for us.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">God did declare His Omnipotence as He said,<b> “I AM THAT I AM.”</b>  Yet we are called to such a personal relationship with the God Almighty.  To our God it doesn’t matter how great and powerful He is.  He wants a real personal relationship with each of us.  Jesus tells us  in <b>Mathew 6:9</b> to address this all powerful, all mighty <b>God as OUR FATHER</b>.  We are not meant to walk this path alone nor in our own strength, but in His power and for His purposes.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">He says,”And from ancient times things that are not yet done, Saying, ‘My counsel shall stand, And I will do all My pleasure.”
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Take hold of who He desires to be for you today and onward into eternity.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Our Father may we come to fully trust in You. We ask forgiveness where our perspective is askew and ask that You give us the ability to seek You in your fullness and receive all that you desire for us.  May we bask in Your continued presence and trust in Your power to sustain us continually.   In Jesus name we pray.  Amen
                                                                        </p>
